  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n'Help to improve Status' popup doesn't disappear after tapping on `No, I don't want to share` or `Share usage` after recovering a user\r\nPlease note, home screen is displayed for several seconds and only after the popup appears. In previous version home screen wasn't displayed before the popup.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nPopup disappears after tapping on `No, I don't want to share` or `Share usage` buttons. Usages is shared or not shared according to the selection.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n'Help to improve Status' popup is present after tapping on `No, I don't want to share` or `Share usage` buttons after user recovering\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- open Status\r\n- Click on 'I already have an account', if the app is fresh installed, or 'Add existing account' if it's not.\r\n- Recover user by entering passphrase and password and tapping on 'Sign in'\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: <img width=\"187\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-05 at 1 44 23 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12611990/38361850-76ebb53e-38d7-11e8-8224-f4fb7488532d.png\">\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Android & iOS",
